r (PAN) cards will not be accepted due to national regulations. Travelers who are not citizens of India must present a valid passport and visa.  Indian citizens must show a PAN card at check-out for cash transactions exceeding INR 25000. Customers may be requested by the property to provide documentation of recent travel history (such as showing passport immigration stamps) and/or complete a health declaration.,Mandatory fees: Guests booked in Breakfast Included rate plans are charged an additional VAT at check-in or check-out.,Optional fees:  - Fee for buffet breakfast: approximately INR 850 per person\n- Airport shuttle fee: INR 4250 per vehicle (one-way, maximum occupancy 4)\n- Pet deposit: INR 3500 per stay\n- Pet fee: INR 3000 per pet, per day\n- Early check-in is available for a fee (subject to availability)\n- Rollaway bed fee: INR 3000.0 per night\n The above list may not be comprehensive. Fees and deposits may not include tax and are subject to change. \n,Know before you go:    - One child 11 years old or younger stays free when occupying the parent or guardian's room, using existing bedding. \n- Only registered guests are allowed in the guestrooms. \n - Free in-room WiFi has a 4-device limit. WiFi in public areas is also free and has a 4-device limit. \n- Contactless check-in and contactless check-out are available.\n- At check-in, guests must provide a record of full COVID-19 vaccination.\n- Guests providing vaccine records must have received complete COVID-19 vaccination at least 3 days prior to check-in.\n ,Tax Recovery Charges and Service Fees for 2 people: 74.05 USD (This amount is included within the total price).,Tax Recovery Charges and Service Fees for 2 people: 73.23 USD (This amount is included within the total price).,Tax Recovery Charges and Service Fees for 2 people: 98.02 USD (This amount is included within the total price).\nCheckIn instructions:   - Extra-person charges may apply and vary depending on property policy\n- Government-issued p