y offers transfers from the airport (surcharges may apply). To arrange pick-up, guests must contact the property 24 hours prior to arrival, using the contact information on the booking confirmation. Front desk staff will greet guests on arrival at the property. At check-in, guests must provide a record of full COVID-19 vaccination. Guests providing vaccine records must have received complete COVID-19 vaccination at least 3 days prior to check-in. For any questions, please contact the property using the information on the booking confirmation. Information provided by the property may be translated using automated translation tools. To register at this property, guests who are Indian citizens must provide a valid photo identity card (Voter's ID, driver's license, Aahdar Card, or any other ID with address approved by the Government of India). Permanent Account Number (PAN) cards will not be accepted due to national regulations. Travelers who are not citizens of India must present a valid passport and visa.  Indian citizens must show a PAN card at check-out for cash transactions exceeding INR 25000. Customers may be requested by the property to provide documentation of recent travel history (such as showing passport immigration stamps) and/or complete a health declaration.,Mandatory fees: Guests booked in Breakfast Included rate plans are charged an additional VAT at check-in or check-out.,Optional fees:  - Fee for buffet breakfast: approximately INR 850 per person\n- Airport shuttle fee: INR 4250 per vehicle (one-way, maximum occupancy 4)\n- Pet deposit: INR 3500 per stay\n- Pet fee: INR 3000 per pet, per day\n- Early check-in is available for a fee (subject to availability)\n- Rollaway bed fee: INR 3000.0 per night\n The above list may not be comprehensive. Fees and deposits may not include tax and are subject to change. \n,Know before you go:    - One child 11 years old or younger stays free when occupying the parent or guardian's room, using existing bedding. \n- On